    "summary": "Piero Medici is an Italian PhD architect, with two degrees: one in Environmental Sciences (BSc in Venice), one in Architecture (BSc in Venice) and a Master degree in Architecture (MSc in TU Delft) with a thesis focussed on sustainability. His doctoral research focuses on European sustainable housing and neighbourhoods during the 1970s.\nHe has 10 years of experience, working as an Architect, Researcher, Lecturer, Environmental Scientist and Sustainability Consultant, in various architectural practices, consultancy offices and academic institutions, including Nicholas Grimshaw & Partners, London (UK), where he was also a member of the Project Sustainability Group; Superuse Studios and Except Integrated Sustainability, Rotterdam (NL); Centre of Excellence for Sustainable Development, University Ca\u2019 Foscari of Venice (IT). He is currently Visiting Researcher/Lecturer at TU Delft. He has been involved in several academic activities in various institutions and publishing different works. He is co-founder of {Co-P-E} Collective of Project in Equipoise, Europan 14 winner.\nHe is a curious, motivated and innovative bioclimatic and passive system architect and environmental scientist always working to find new solutions in order to improve the environment and to strengthen the built environment. Some of his focus has been on sustainable bioclimatic, low-energy, passive building and urban design; research on sustainable solutions, evaluating environmental impact of materials, their risk of toxicity for human health and for the environment; calculating Life Cycle Assessment, Life Cycle Costs of building\u2019s materials, building physics and energy performance; integrated sustainable, strategic design and planning of buildings neighbourhoods, cities, regions.\n\n",
